docker

tradational arch vs virtulzation

tradational arch -> hardware -> os -> applications 
virtualaztion -> hardware -> virutal layer (hyperisor) -> VM (os + appilcation)

hypervisor 
    type 1 bare metal- h/w -> hypervisor -> vm (os+appilcation) e.g cloud platform 
    type 2 Hosted -  h/w -> host os -> hypervisor -> vm (guest os+ applcication) e.g vmware

Containerization 
is a lightweight virtualization method where applications run in isolated environments called containers, sharing the host OS kernel while maintaining their own dependencies and configurations.

h/w -> hosted os ->container enginer (docker engine) -> container (lightweight os + app+ library)

if app stops deleted container will also stops.
-> give resource to h/w ->bootup time low

